collections.name: Tulip Mania - Puzzle
collections.description:
A favorite pasttime of mine involves *extremely long gazes at brushstrokes on an artwork. You can find me at any art museum a few inches away (when allowed) from any piece of work, wishing my eyes could magnify into the artist's paint strokes (hoping that I could enter their mind while they were painting). 

This Tulip Mania collection is focused on close up photographs (1-2 inches) of my original oil works on canvas. I have intentionally left some pieces with "imperfect" debris because I want YOU to see the rawness of the canvas, as best as your eyes and the computer screen can allow.

The purpose is clear, are you able to fit the pieces of each photo to the corresponding painting? What additional oddities are you able to identify in the photos? 

I welcome dialogue and chatter and most of all, excitement. 

Perhaps one day, we can enjoy this little game in person in a museum with all works on display for review. Until then, let's enjoy it together online.
